      "side": 1,
      "message": "[error] Line 343: The remote payload trusts `cid` and `did` from untrusted JSON. A malicious peer can send a collaborative-editing IM that names a different conversation/document and have this daemon apply updates or emit cursor/document signals for that target. The authenticated/envelope conversation id should be passed into `onRemotePayload` and used as the authority, rejecting mismatches.\n```suggestion\nvoid CollaborativeEditing::onRemotePayload(const std::string\u0026 from,\n                                           const std::string\u0026 conversationId,\n                                           const std::string\u0026 jsonPayload)\n{\n    Json::Value root;\n    if (!json::parse(jsonPayload, root))\n        return;\n    if (root.get(\"cid\", \"\").asString() !\u003d conversationId)\n        return;\n    auto documentId \u003d root[\"did\"].asString();\n    if (documentId.empty())\n        return;\n```",
