      "message": "[warning] Line 367: Remote CRDT updates are decoded and applied with no size limit. Since this is reachable from peer messages, a large base64 payload can force large allocations and expensive CRDT processing. Enforce a maximum payload/update size before decoding/applying, consistent with the IM/message limits.\n```suggestion\n    const auto encoded \u003d root[\"u\"].asString();\n    if (encoded.size() \u003e MAX_COLLAB_UPDATE_BASE64_SIZE)\n        return;\n    auto update \u003d base64::decode(encoded);\n    if (update.empty() || update.size() \u003e MAX_COLLAB_UPDATE_SIZE)\n        return;\n```",
